quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  22,56,On that Day all control will belong to God. He will judge between them. Those who believe and do good deeds shall enter the Gardens of Bliss
  22,57,but those who deny the truth and deny Our signs will receive a humiliating punishment
  22,58,"As for those who left their homes for the cause of God and then were slain or died, God will give them a generous provision. Surely God is the Best of Providers"
  22,59,He will admit them to a place with which they shall be well-pleased. For God is all knowing and most forbearing
  22,60,"Thus it shall be. As for one who retaliates to the same extent as he has suffered and then is again wronged, God will surely come to his aid. God is merciful and forgiving"
  22,61,That is because God makes the night pass into the day and makes the day pass into the night. God is all hearing and all seeing
  22,62,"That is because God is the Truth while anything they invoke besides God is sheer falsehood. God is the Sublime, the Great One"
  22,63,"Have you not seen how God sends down water from sky, whereupon the earth becomes green? God is unfathomable, and all aware"
  22,64,"all that is in the heavens and on the earth belongs to Him. Surely, God is self-sufficient and praiseworthy"